race.comment: Tough and go wide. SUNDAY BUZZ (3) has been racing in stronger grade over longer and will find this easier than Moonee Valley last time.  Three back he led when narrowly beaten at Warrnambool and is suited in this contest. Has to drop back 600m but this is his best trip and he should have the versatility to manage. JENNI THE TANK (8) hasn't fired since the barn switch but she's right up to this at best. She's won at this trip and Coffey rides and will position forward from an inside gate. Gets her chance in this lineup. KODIAK BEAR (1) showed plenty last preparation and has had two conditioning runs off a 318-day spell. This distance is more his go and he has the blinkers applied for the first time. Expect quick improvement. COSMOS FACTORY (6) also looks a chance in a tricky race.
